  "text": "Our problem is very similar, structurally, to the problem of computing extremal black hole entropy. The CFT partition function can be regarded as the \"microscopic\" result for the partition function. The leading large N result (1.5) is the analogue of the BekensteinHawking or Wald entropy. We then expect the subleading logarithmic correction (1.7) to be reproduced by a one-loop correction in Euclidean quantum gravity on AdS 4 × X 7 , as in [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
